values:
&nbsp;Annoyingly anxious tonight. What's new.&nbsp;

Had a mostly awesome weekend. Friday night I&nbsp;drank lots of wine with Cliff and Christine and played rockband (not very well after a bottle of wine). It was nice to sit around with friends and just talk. We all were probably a little to drunk for our own good, but it was thoroughly wonderful. Saturday night we went dancing. Jakes was a little lame and the dj wasn't great but dancing was awesome. Me and Christine seriously rocked it. I&nbsp;think I&nbsp;had forgotten how much I&nbsp;missed my friends. &nbsp;

Saturday was a little bit of a disaster. Went for a walk with my friend and her boyfriend. Problem is I&nbsp;really really can't stand him. Like he is everything I&nbsp;hate. The only thing that could make it worse is if he were a republican. Anyway, things were fine and I&nbsp;was being nice until he brought up a subject that really pisses me off. He was being seriously atagonistic. He could have just stopped at any point, so I&nbsp;don't think that this is really all my fault. But anyway. I&nbsp;lost my temper and went off on him. I&nbsp;literally told him how stupid he was, that I&nbsp;was smarter than him and that he was an idiot and should really stop speaking and listen to somebody more intelligent. Bitchy, but true actually, he is really ignorant and not all that bright. Anyway, after 10 minutes of yelling at him we went out seperate ways. I&nbsp;would have just stopped the whole thing and walked away but we were walking around the lake... not really anywhere to go.&nbsp;

Anyway, I&nbsp;don;t think she is talking to me. I&nbsp;did call and apologize... but i dunno. I&nbsp;am torn because on the one hand I&nbsp;actually believe everything I&nbsp;said, but on the other it was probably a little out of line for me to say it. But isn't it fair for me not to want him in my life? I&nbsp;love her but I&nbsp;don't like him, so why do I&nbsp;have to be around him. I'm just frustrated I&nbsp;guess. I&nbsp;have lost a lot of girlfriends lately. A lot of friends in general. And part of me is beginning to wonder if it really is 'cause I&nbsp;am a bitch. I&nbsp;always assumed it was because these people were unreasonable/immature/crazy. But what if it really is me?&nbsp;

Enough whining. Love to all of my friends who still speak to me :-)&nbsp;

&nbsp;Another wave of debilitating anxiety the last day or so. Started last night around 6 or so and hasn't go away. I haven't eaten much because of it. I&nbsp;kinda bring it on myself. I wouldn't be so anxious if I&nbsp;kept up with my work and did my job the way that I&nbsp;should. But then my anxiety gets in the way of me doing my job right. Vicious circle. Complaining doesn't really help. But my god it hurts.&nbsp;

Chris is in Olympia for the weekend. It is weird having the apartment to myself. I&nbsp;have litterally never in my life lived alone. So being alone in the apartment is novel and not entirely unpleasant. But I&nbsp;do miss Chris and his hugs. On the other hand though, if he were here I&nbsp;would probably be a bitch, as I am wont to do when I&nbsp;am anxious, so maybe it is good I&nbsp;am by myself, since I&nbsp;am not fit company.&nbsp;

Now I&nbsp;am watching LA Ink which I&nbsp;adore although I&nbsp;think it has gotten to be more about the drama and less about the tattooing. But still an awesome show. I&nbsp;think I&nbsp;should put some pants on and go buy some wine. This is the kind of night where that is appropriate. And I&nbsp;have a fuck ton of work to do.&nbsp;

Sometimes, when I&nbsp;feel like this, I&nbsp;wish I&nbsp;could talk to somebody who would understand the exact way in which it hurts. The closest thing I&nbsp;can think of is a combination of stage fright and the utter, inescapable desolation of a major loss like breaking up, something like that. But that isn't really the way it feels, just the closest I&nbsp;can get.&nbsp;

Anyway, time for work and wine. Or more likely, wine and work

I think that from now on LJ is going to be somewhere where I&nbsp;record complete randomness rather than morose, self-pitying depth. Don't get me wrong, for all of you who like that, I&nbsp;am sure it will come up here and there. But here comes some randomness for today.&nbsp;

I&nbsp;have a love hate relationship with coffee. On the one hand, it makes me anxious and crazy. But on the other, this is the first time I&nbsp;have felt truely awake in about 5 days. I&nbsp;have been coming home and just passing out, in this scary kind of coma sleep where it is really hard to wake up and I&nbsp;can't think. And sleep seems like the most important thing in the whole world to me. And that sounds like a blood sugar problem. But I&nbsp;have been eating okay. So basically I&nbsp;need to eat better, and workout more. I probably have blood sugar issues because I&nbsp;grew up eating crap, weight to much, and my workout involves me walking up three flights of stairs to my office. Anyway, I&nbsp;like coffee

My boss is still out of town. I&nbsp;don't see her coming back anytime soon. Which means that we are all on our own... which had me really stressed this morning. Then I&nbsp;thought, fuck it, it is just a job, I&nbsp;will figure it the fuck out. Besides, at least my brother isn't unconscious in the ICU.&nbsp;

It is way to fucking hot, and there is no air conditioning in my office. There is air conditioning in the place where we do call time, so that almost makes up for me having to spend so much time here. The poor ferrets look really pitiful. Chris keeps dunking them in water to keep them cool, which they don't like much but at least it keeps them from heat stroke.&nbsp;&nbsp;I&nbsp;told Chris to go to his parents so he and the ferrets could stay cool until this heat wave was over, but he wont go because he says I&nbsp;don't know how to feed myself. Which may or may not be true.&nbsp;

23 days till the primary. 22 if you don't count today.&nbsp;

There was something else I&nbsp;wanted to say, but I&nbsp;can't think what it is, so I suppose that I&nbsp;wont. Getting back to work now. Hope all is well with everybody else.

&nbsp;Remember that last post where I&nbsp;said I&nbsp;was fucked because I&nbsp;had 8 events to plan? Yeah, now I&nbsp;might have 14. One of which is goaled at a minimum of $10,000. Fuck.&nbsp;

One of the girls I&nbsp;kinda work with (who I severely dislike for a multitude of reasons that I will not go into here) just found out that her aunt has cancer so she is flying down to California tonight. And my boss doesn't bet back until Monday. And the girl I&nbsp;work with has two huge events next week. I have know idea what is going on with them, how many people are coming, who is coming, who is catering... or anything else. And she is already on a plane.&nbsp;

So I am pretty well and truly fucked. Gotta love politics.&nbsp;
